video.title: Saved by the Bell
video.synopsis: From middle school to college, best friends Zack, Kelly, Slater, Jessie, Screech and Lisa take on the highs and lows of life together in this hit series.

episodes.synopsis: Eighth-grader Zack runs into a ninth-grader he met during the summer — and lied to about his age.
episodes.title: Summer Love

episodes.synopsis: Complications of the romantic kind arise when Miss Bliss intercepts a love note intended for Lisa.
episodes.title: Love Letters

episodes.synopsis: Zack hopes he can make enough money on the stock market to pay for damages done to his father's VCR.
episodes.title: Wall Street

episodes.synopsis: A student's refusal to dissect a frog in biology class sparks a controversy among her peers.
episodes.title: Leaping to Conclusions

episodes.synopsis: Zack won't admit it, but he's disturbed by the chemistry between his father and his teacher.
episodes.title: Parents and Teachers

episodes.synopsis: The gang encourages Screech to stand up to a bully, unaware of the reason behind the boy's tough exterior.
episodes.title: The Showdown

episodes.synopsis: At a school mixer, Zack encourages a friend to ask a girl to dance — but the girl would rather dance with Zack.
episodes.title: Save the Last Dance for Me

episodes.synopsis: Principal Belding smells a rat when the school is plagued by rodents just as Zack is due to take an important midterm.
episodes.title: The Boy Who Cried Rat

episodes.synopsis: An argument among students over a class project helps Miss Bliss clear up her differences with a longtime friend.
episodes.title: Let's Get Together

episodes.synopsis: Screech is put on a classroom trial when he takes the fall for pulling a prank on Miss Bliss.
episodes.title: Practical Jokes

episodes.synopsis: Zack bets he can plant a kiss on a pop singer who's giving her final performance at school before going on to college.
episodes.title: Stevie

episodes.synopsis: Anxious to click with a cool campus clique, Zack agrees to insult his friends.
episodes.title: Clubs and Cliques

episodes.synopsis: Principal Belding disapproves of the unconventional teacher substituting for Miss Bliss's history class.
episodes.title: The Mentor

episodes.synopsis: The gang decides to enter a national dance contest held at The Max.
episodes.title: Dancing to the Max

episodes.synopsis: When Lisa spends too much on her father's credit card, the group sells Lisa's clothes to raise money to pay him back.
episodes.title: The Lisa Card

episodes.synopsis: After getting struck by lightning, Screech becomes able to foretell the future.
episodes.title: The Gift

episodes.synopsis: Kelly has to choose between Zack and Slater as her date to a big Bayside dance.
episodes.title: Fatal Distraction

episodes.synopsis: To help an ego-deflated Screech, Zack poses as Bambi, a girl with a crush on Screech.
episodes.title: Screech's Woman

episodes.synopsis: When Slater's dad wants to move to Hawaii, Zack devises a scheme to make Slater want to leave so Zack can have Kelly all to himself.
episodes.title: Aloha Slater

episodes.synopsis: A handsome teacher substitutes for Miss Simpson, and all the girls fall for him.
episodes.title: The Substitute

episodes.synopsis: Zack and Screech think they've come up with a cure for zits when a science experiment backfires.
episodes.title: Cream for a Day

episodes.synopsis: Zack bets a bully his dirt bike that Slater will win a wrestling match.
episodes.title: Pinned to the Mat

episodes.synopsis: When Screech tutors Kelly ahead of a midterm, she starts to look at him differently.
episodes.title: Beauty and the Screech

episodes.synopsis: For a class project, the group starts a successful business selling friendship bracelets — until Zack develops a thirst for power and money.
episodes.title: The Friendship Business

episodes.synopsis: A new class project has the gang acting like married couples for a week.
episodes.title: The Mamas and the Papas

episodes.synopsis: When Kelly suffers an injury, the group looks after her baby brother — at school.
episodes.title: The Baby Sitters

episodes.synopsis: When Zack discovers that the new student body president will win a trip to Washington, D.C., he runs against Jessie solely for the perk.
episodes.title: The Election

episodes.synopsis: Zack puts subliminal messages on Kelly's rock tape to persuade her to ask him to dance.
episodes.title: The Zack Tapes

episodes.synopsis: This episode follows the gang on the first day of high school at Bayside, where Zack vows to win over Kelly Kapowski and meets A.C. Slater.
episodes.title: King of the Hill

episodes.synopsis: It's the homecoming game against Valley, and the two schools play their annual round of pranks.
episodes.title: Save That Tiger

episodes.synopsis: When the gang needs money to replace the school video camera, they enter a contest that gives a prize for the best photo of an alien.
episodes.title: Close Encounters of the Nerd Kind

episodes.synopsis: After his friends and parents forget his birthday, Screech carries out his revenge by becoming a tyrannical hall monitor.
episodes.title: Screech's Birthday

episodes.synopsis: When Slater's pet chameleon dies, the gang tries to replace the lizard with another — without Slater noticing.
episodes.title: Slater's Friend

episodes.synopsis: Zack and Slater vie to take Kelly to the prom, but Kelly might not be able to go at all after she finds out news about her father.
episodes.title: The Prom

episodes.synopsis: An ROTC official comes to Bayside for new recruits.
episodes.title: Zack's War

episodes.synopsis: The pals host a radiothon for money to save the Max.
episodes.title: Save the Max

episodes.synopsis: The group gets a lesson in responsible driving.
episodes.title: Driver's Education

episodes.synopsis: Screech's parents go out of town and leave Screech and Zack alone in the house.
episodes.title: House Party

episodes.synopsis: Jessie and Zack both have blind dates.
episodes.title: Blind Dates

episodes.synopsis: Zack hires an actor to play his dad for a conference at school.
episodes.title: Rent-A-Pop

episodes.synopsis: Zack enters Screech in a Homecoming Queen contest.
episodes.title: Miss Bayside

episodes.synopsis: Jessie becomes hooked on caffeine pills to keep up with all of her activities.
episodes.title: Jessie's Song

episodes.synopsis: To make money, Zack sells calendars with pictures of the girls without their knowledge.
episodes.title: Model Students

episodes.synopsis: Zack and Slater get a 900 number and set up an advice hotline for teens.
episodes.title: 1-900 Crushed

episodes.synopsis: Zack deals with the death of a friend.
episodes.title: Running Zack

episodes.synopsis: Zack asks Kelly to go steady — but he has a small change of heart when he meets the school nurse who's giving everyone flu shots.
episodes.title: From Nurse to Worse

episodes.synopsis: Belding's younger and hipper brother substitute teaches and breaks most of the rules to get on the students' good side.
episodes.title: The Fabulous Belding Boys

episodes.synopsis: Jessie and Slater, Zack and Kelly, and Mr. and Mrs. Belding have relationship crises at the same time.
episodes.title: Breaking Up Is Hard to Undo

episodes.synopsis: The group joins the glee club in hopes of winning a contest and a trip to Hawaii.
episodes.title: The Glee Club

episodes.synopsis: As the students prepare for the costume ball, Kelly lands a job at The Max, which affects her relationship with Zack.
episodes.title: The Last Dance

episodes.synopsis: Zack's friends set him up on numerous dates and he tries to make Kelly jealous. Lisa has her Sweet 16 party.
episodes.title: The Aftermath

episodes.synopsis: Zack is scared about having surgery on his knee as Lisa's mother performs the operation.
episodes.title: Operation Zack

episodes.synopsis: Screech lands in the chess tournament finals and must compete against a Russian player.
episodes.title: Check Your Mate

episodes.synopsis: Zack, Screech and Slater make fake IDs to get into a club, where they spot Kelly's boyfriend with another girl.
episodes.title: Fake IDs

episodes.synopsis: Zack nurses a duck back to health. When oil is found under Bayside, the gang dreams of getting rich but soon learns its effects on the environment.
episodes.title: Pipe Dreams

episodes.synopsis: Jessie's mother marries a man with a son from New York who soon builds a reputation for playing tricks on everyone.
episodes.title: The Wicked Stepbrother: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Jessie's stepbrother develops romantic feelings for someone at school and continues to scheme against Zack and Slater.
episodes.title: The Wicked Stepbrother: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: To raise funds for new cheerleading uniforms, Bayside auctions off dates to the spring dance.
episodes.title: Date Auction

episodes.synopsis: Jessie worries her SAT scores will keep her from getting into her dream college while Zack's test results bring new challenges.
episodes.title: SATs

episodes.synopsis: When a student is discriminated against during tryouts for the wrestling team, Zack and the group take matters into their own hands.
episodes.title: Hold Me Tight

episodes.synopsis: A famous movie star comes to Bayside to film an antidrug PSA. He turns out to be a hypocrite who smokes pot.
episodes.title: No Hope with Dope

episodes.synopsis: Zack's poor attendance record prevents him from participating in Cut Day.
episodes.title: Cut Day

episodes.synopsis: With the arrival of a new student at Bayside, Slater asks Zack for help with hiding his relationship but winds up in a romantic dilemma.
episodes.title: Love Machine

episodes.synopsis: Zack comes up with a fresh idea for the yearbook but decides to use some of the tapes to his own advantage.
episodes.title: The Video Yearbook

episodes.synopsis: The group performs a classic fairy tale for the annual school play — with a twist.
episodes.title: Snow White and the Seven Dorks

episodes.synopsis: The group starts their summer jobs at a beach club and tries to sneak in after hours to throw a surprise birthday party for Zack.
episodes.title: Zack's Birthday Party

episodes.synopsis: When the Malibu Beach Club takes on a rival in a volleyball game, Zack promises a guy a date with Kelly so he can play on the team.
episodes.title: The Game

episodes.synopsis: Zack must name the winner of the Miss Liberty beauty pageant — and the contestants are Lisa, Jessie, Kelly and Stacey.
episodes.title: Fourth of July

episodes.synopsis: Ahead of the annual charity ATV race, Stacey's college boyfriend shows up unexpectedly.
episodes.title: My Boyfriend's Back

episodes.synopsis: Mr. Carosi leaves Stacey in charge of the club and has mistakenly books two parties for the same night.
episodes.title: Boss Lady

episodes.synopsis: As Stacey prepares to head back to Boston, the group wraps up their jobs at the beach club.
episodes.title: The Last Weekend

episodes.synopsis: When the gang finds $5,000 at the mall, Zack decides to "invest" it in concert tickets and turn a profit before returning the money.
episodes.title: All in the Mall

episodes.synopsis: The gang goes to a resort in Palm Springs for Jessie's father's wedding. Slater meets a princess from another country.
episodes.title: Palm Springs Weekend: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Jessie plans to sabotage her father's wedding as Slater tries to impress Christina's royal family.
episodes.title: Palm Springs Weekend: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Zack has a fantasy that the group becomes famous rock stars.
episodes.title: Rockumentary

episodes.synopsis: Zack, Slater, Screech, Kelly, and Jessie take up holiday jobs at the mall, where they meet a homeless man.
episodes.title: Home for Christmas: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: As Zack's mom prepares to put on a Christmas play at the mall, the group helps Laura and her father get back on their feet.
episodes.title: Home for Christmas: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: The gang spends the weekend at a murder mystery mansion. Zack winds up as the accused murderer and must get himself off the hook.
episodes.title: Mystery Weekend

episodes.synopsis: When Zack and Slater try to date a transfer student from Idaho, their friendship takes a turn.
episodes.title: The Fight

episodes.synopsis: When the students and teachers switch places for the week, Kelly and Slater clash while Zack takes his power as principal a little too far.
episodes.title: Student-Teacher Week

episodes.synopsis: The group sells Screech's grandmother's spaghetti sauce on a cable access show.
episodes.title: Screech's Spaghetti Sauce

episodes.synopsis: A romantic pair in the group leaves Screech feeling upset.
episodes.title: The Bayside Triangle

episodes.synopsis: A.C. and Maj. Slater fight over where A.C. should attend college. Jessie becomes a cheerleader.
episodes.title: Wrestling with the Future

episodes.synopsis: From passionate pursuits to heart-wrenching breakups, this episode looks back on the group's love stories.
episodes.title: Isn't It Romantic?

episodes.synopsis: Zack and Slater egg on a teachers' strike, putting the annual Academic Bowl in jeopardy.
episodes.title: The Teacher's Strike

episodes.synopsis: With ticket sales low, the group tries to come up with a way to salvage the prom. Zack eyes a date who's already said yes to someone else.
episodes.title: The Senior Prom

episodes.synopsis: The gang at Bayside in 2003 find a video left by students in 1993 in this flashback episode set in the future.
episodes.title: The Time Capsule

episodes.synopsis: As graduation day approaches, Zack discovers he needs one more credit to graduate and Jessie stresses over being valedictorian.
episodes.title: Graduation

episodes.synopsis: Lisa tries to come up with ideas for the annual Fall Ball. Zack deals with a new student at Bayside who supposedly takes his parking space.
episodes.title: The New Girl

episodes.synopsis: The students set up a hotline at Bayside to provide a safe space for teens struggling with their problems.
episodes.title: Teen-Line

episodes.synopsis: Zack and Slater make a bet involving Tori. But when she discovers their scheme, she plots revenge.
episodes.title: Masquerade Ball

episodes.synopsis: Zack's plans to win a trip to Hawaii backfire and land everyone in detention.
episodes.title: Day of Detention

episodes.synopsis: After drinking at a party, the group decides to drive home in Lisa's mother's car and gets into an accident.
episodes.title: Drinking and Driving

episodes.synopsis: Zack negotiates with a shady salesperson to strike a deal on class rings for the senior class.
episodes.title: Class Rings

episodes.synopsis: When an alumnus of Bayside leaves the school money, the students fight over who gets to spend it. So Mr. Belding hosts a sports competition.
episodes.title: The Will

episodes.synopsis: When Slater's sister visits Bayside, Zack tries to make a move.
episodes.title: Slater's Sister

episodes.synopsis: During an earthquake, Tori, Zack and Mrs. Belding get trapped in the faculty elevator.
episodes.title: Earthquake

episodes.synopsis: Zack looks back on fond summer memories at Malibu Sands.
episodes.title: The Best Summer of My Life

episodes.synopsis: The gang comes up with an idea to write a new school song as their senior class gift to Bayside.
episodes.title: School Song

episodes.synopsis: On the island, Zack makes a connection as Lisa, Slater and Jessie make a bet. Screech is believed to be the descendant of a local legend.
episodes.title: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: After the gang sabotages their stay with the competition, Mr. Belding's tour group is lured to Kelly's grandfather's hotel — with mixed results.
episodes.title: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Kelly's new romance may not be what it seems, while Zack's situation has some surprises of its own. The group hosts an elaborate luau on the beach.
episodes.title: Part 3

episodes.synopsis: Brian's subterfuge leaves the resort's fate hanging in the balance, but Zack hatches a plan to help Kelly's grandfather and a native tribe.
episodes.title: Part 4

episodes.synopsis: Roommates Zack, Screech and Slater arrive at college and discover that they don't have their suite all to themselves.
episodes.title: Pilot

episodes.synopsis: Just as Zack hits it off with Leslie, the arrival of a new transfer student complicates matters. Screech assembles a bicycle.
episodes.title: Guess Who's Coming to College

episodes.synopsis: Slater tries to bulk up to join a new wrestling weight class. Screech solicits Mike's help to get buff. Zack receives a unique anthropology assignment.
episodes.title: Zack, Lies & Video Tape

episodes.synopsis: When Zack and Slater both try to pledge the same fraternity, they give Screech a mini-makeover to try and prevent him from hurting their prospects.
episodes.title: Rush Week

episodes.synopsis: Slater makes a connection that proves to be culturally enlightening. Zack organizes a ski trip. Screech loses a lab mouse.
episodes.title: Slater's War

episodes.synopsis: Leslie asks Screech to the homecoming banquet to throw her overbearing parents for a loop. Zack is awed by a revered alumnus.
episodes.title: The Homecoming

episodes.synopsis: Kelly, Leslie and Alex compete for the attention of their karate instructor while Zack, Slater and Screech set Mike up on a date.
episodes.title: The Poker Game

episodes.synopsis: Zack poses as Professor Lasky to impress an admirer as Slater and Screech pose for a pinup calendar Kelly and Alex are putting together.
episodes.title: Professor Zack

episodes.synopsis: Zack asks Screech to tutor the tennis player he is dating, causing an unexpected conflict between the two friends.
episodes.title: Screech Love

episodes.synopsis: Kelly's new job starts to impact her academic life. Mike gets invited to try out for the San Francisco 49ers but thinks he's out of shape.
episodes.title: Dr. Kelly

episodes.synopsis: Car troubles leave the gang stuck at school over Thanksgiving. An injured Mike prepares a special dinner for kids in need.
episodes.title: A Thanksgiving Story

episodes.synopsis: Zack prepares to take a big step with Kelly just as she finds herself developing feelings for someone else. Screech befriends a chimpanzee.
episodes.title: Teacher's Pet

episodes.synopsis: A jealous Zack publicizes Kelly's new relationship. Screech and Alex receive similar scores on a compatibility test.
episodes.title: Kelly And the Professor

episodes.synopsis: Struggling with an ethics course taught by a tough professor, the group faces a dilemma when Zack gets his hands on a copy of the midterm exam.
episodes.title: A Question of Ethics

episodes.synopsis: To try and raise funds for a trip to Mexico, Zack decides to host a rave party at the dorm while Mike is away.
episodes.title: The Rave

episodes.synopsis: Alex questions Slater's commitment. Zack takes a job at the health center to be closer to Kelly. Screech considers getting a tattoo.
episodes.title: Bedside Manner

episodes.synopsis: The sudden death of a beloved professor inspires Zack to adopt a new attitude on life.
episodes.title: Love And Death

episodes.synopsis: When Kelly gets accepted into a special summer program, Zack makes a bold move. Meanwhile, Slater feels guilty after going out with another girl.
episodes.title: Marry Me

episodes.synopsis: While planning a major event, Zack and Kelly face opposition from friends and family, but the arrival of a familiar face helps put them at ease.
episodes.title: Wedding Plans

episodes.synopsis: The boys head home for a visit, and Zack clashes with his dad. Then, the gang hits the road for Las Vegas – which gets off to a bumpy start.
episodes.title: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: After a corrupt cop shakes down Zack, the guys try to figure out how to earn enough cash in Vegas to pay for the wedding celebration.
episodes.title: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Zack tries to keep his secret scheme from Kelly. Screech winds up at a dance club. Slater steps up to Carla's ex-boyfriend.
episodes.title: Part 3

episodes.synopsis: After the gang outsmarts a crew of crooks, Zack and Kelly's big day finally arrives.
episodes.title: Part 4
